cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a framework for accelerating and compressing CNN models for computer vision tasks by enabling them to infer on one thumbnail image. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the training strategies and the effectiveness of the proposed framework, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves image downscaling, which is related to cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with reducing computational resources, which is related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
